15/02/2005
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- At a ceremony in Brussels Monday (14 February), Macedonian Prime Minister Vlado Buckovski submitted detailed written answers to the European Commission questionnaire, a key step along the country's road to EU membership. 
He emphasised that Macedonia hopes to obtain official candidate status by the end of this year. 
While in Brussels, Buckovski also met with NATO Secretary General Jaap de Hoop Scheffer, who welcomed the progress Macedonia has made in implementing defence reforms and the Membership Action Plan.
In other news Monday, the ODIHR officially opened its observation mission for the 13 March local elections in Macedonia. 
In addition to long-term staff, the OSCE/ODIHR mission plans the deployment of 250 short-term observers across the country. 
(Utrinski Vesnik, Vest - 15/02/05; EU Web site, OSCE Web site, A1 TV - 14/02/05)
